      "message": "It does do something.  If we don\u0027t set this, we\u0027d expect to build and use third_party/externals/expat.  This says to Skia, you can use expat (skia_use_expat is true by default) but when you do use the system version instead of building it yourself.\n\nThere are three modes we can be in:\n1)  Skia code requiring expat is not built;\n2)  Skia code requiring expat is built, linking against expat we build;\n3)  Skia code requiring expat is built, linking against the system expat.\n\nThis puts us in mode 3.",
